Cloudy and calm.  This is the last report.
Overcast- windy- and the lake level is below normal.
Lake level up 2".  Sunny and calm.
Overcast and it is a very warm day.
Sunny- water is calm and warm.
A bit breezy but pleasant and sunny- algae blooms in the water.
Crisp- clear- calm day- last reading for 1987.
Calm- sunny.  Water level: very low.
Sunny- cool- slightly breezy- some algae.
Overcast- and the temperature is 62 F.
Sunny- clear- little breeze- water temperature 41 F.
Overcast- windy- heavy rain earlier in A.M.
Windy- 12 hours after heavy rain- algae level up.
Little breeze- 81 F- algae level up but lake very clear over sand bars.
Temp. 89 F- two eagles and loons daily visitors.
Light overcast- wind 7 mph- 86 F- humid.
Beautiful sunny warm day for October- slight breeze.
Slight breeze- air 60 F- water 54 F.
Sunny- calm- 64 F- N wind 3-5 mph.
Cold- windy- crisp day- water very clear.
Clear- ripples- 2 eagles- 2 loons in A.M.
Sunny- algae- 2 loons-3 eagles-1 osprey sighted.
Very nice day- 64 F- calm- clear.
Nice day- 75 F- calm- weedy on north end- two loons and an eagle sighted.
Breezy- clear- 90 F- 2 loons- 1 eagle sighted.
Lots of pollen on lake the past two weeks.
A bit overcast- windy and cool.
Too cold to swim or ski!  Very calm cool morning + sunny.
One eagle - 3 loons.  Weed problem north end!
Lots of weeds this year!  beautiful sunny morning.  Past weeks weeds have been very bad-floating to shore-could be loosened by motorboats- (coon tail mostly) .

Water extremely clear.  80 degrees- unusually bright clear water!  Very heavy weed growth over much of the lake (coontail) .  First time I ever hit the bottom with secchi disk!  It was our best summer day of the season!!!!
Lake beautiful except for weeds.  Beautiful sunny day- 70 degrees- slight breeze (many weeds 111-coontail) .
Too cold to swim or ski.
Public perception due to cold weather.  Cloudy-cool 50 degrees-windy.
Water color not due to algae.  Overcast + windy- 80 degrees.
Beautiful for a fall day!  55 degrees-sunny.
Sunny- breezy- ice went out May 12th.
Lots of pollen in the water.  Beautiful- sunny- calm day.
Too cold!  Overcast day + calm- 55 degrees.
Beautiful- calm- sunny.  Too cold to swim.
Sunny- partly cloudy- 60 degrees- slight wind.
Unseasonal!  Very beautiful warm sunny breezy day.  60 degrees F.
Sunny.  Little breeze.  80 degrees F.  Great day to be on the lake!
Sunny- beautiful day.  Windy (a busy 4th of July boating weekend plus hard rain caused less clarity) .
Not quite as much lake traffic.  Water clarity improved.
Sunny- slightly breezy- 70 degrees.  Can sense "fall" is in the air!
Sunny- breezy- 60 degrees F.  Fall in the air + water.  Still water.  Skiing.
Warm- slightly windy- sunny- 55 degrees. F- very clear water.
Sunny- windy- water not quite as clear as last reading.
Sunny- slight wind- warm- 70 degrees F.
A calm- sunny- beautiful day. 50 degrees F.
A partly sunny- slightly windy day. 68 degrees F.
Cool- clear- sunny day. 45 degrees F.-too cold for water sports.
Cool- sunny 55 degrees F.- too cold for water sports.
The temperature is 68 degrees- windy and sunny.  Beautiful day.
The temperature is 75 degrees- warm- slightly windy- and a bit overcast.
The temperature is 70 degrees and slightly breeze.  Beautiful summer day.
The temperature is 85 degrees- very hot and humid so a swim is the only way to cool off!
The temperature is 60 degrees- slightly windy- partly sunny- and Fall is in the air.
The temperature is 65 degrees- beautiful sunny- Fall day but too cold for water sports.
60 F. Very nice- calm spring day (Finally). Lake too cold for water sports.
70 F. Beautiful first day of summer. Calm- will be quite warm and humid.
65 F. Welcomed cooling down after 90 degree weather. Beautiful for everything.
80 F. Warm- slightly windy. Great sunny summer day.
Beautiful day. 75 F. Very calm and quiet.
68 F. Sunny- slightly breezy. Beautiful fall day. Trees are beginning to color.
5mph South wind- partly sunny- humid- light rain yesterday morning- yesterday was very windy. current temp. 80.6 deg. F.
8 mph North wind- partly sunny- humid- heavy rain yesterday (~.70in recorded).  Constant cold fronts moving through area. ambient air temp. 47.3 deg. F.
Calm wind- High cirrus clouds- beautiful clear blue sky day with high barometric pressure conditions. Ambient air temperature is 45.5 deg. F.
10 mph South wind- partly cloudy- himid conditions.  Light rain yesterday evening with a long and hot dry spell.  91 Deg. F. ambient air temperature.
5 mph south wind- clear sky- very dry conditions with a long hot dry spell.  80 Deg. F. ambient air temperature.
5 mph south wind- high stratus clouds- no rain for 5 days.  Ambient air temperature 67.8 Deg. F.
10 mph West wind- Partly cloudy day- recent heavy rains  greater than  4" downfall ~ 1 wk ago- ambient temp. 71 Deg.
Calm southeast wind- 3-5 mph- clear skies- rain yesterday afternoon (06/10).  Ambient temp. 79.1 Deg. F.
Calm south wnds- overcast skies- slight rain last night with very little rain for the last 1.5 wks.  ambient temp 71.4 Deg. F.
Moderate West winds- clear skies- no rain for ~1.5 wks.  (71.6 Deg. F.)
3-5mph North winds- Clear skies- No rain for 3 days  (ambient temp. 70.8 Deg. F.)
Sunny day- week after heavy rains.  Windy.
Sunny.  Seagulls.  Five to six boats out waterskiing.
1 day after rainfall.  Quite a bit of weeds and algae on top of surface of Bass Lake.  Noticiable algae bloom on surface.
My son did the test. Partly cloudy.
Added by Betty.  Windy- partly cloudy becoming clearer temp about 67 degrees F
ice out 04/26/2020 Very windy- helped ice go out- did not go out in the "usual" pattern due to wind?
